<H2><U>
Native American Legends About Squirrels
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><B><A HREF="
http://culture.delawaretribe.org/stories.htm
">When Squirrels Were Huge</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://www.acaciart.com/stories/archive5.html
">Klouskap Squirrel Tale</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <b><A HREF="
http://pyramidmesa.netfirms.com/passam1.html
">Glooscap Shrinks the Animals</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <B><A HREF="
http://www.bigorrin.org/archive1.htm
">Gluskabe the Transformer</a></b> <IMG SRC="star.gif" ALT="*"> <B><A HREF="
http://www.nativeamericanembassy.net/www.lenni-lenape.com/www/html/LenapeArchives/LenapeSet-01/squirrel.html
">The Giant Squirrel</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Algonquian legends about how the squirrel got its small size.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.firstpeople.us/FP-Html-Legends/EclipseOfTheSunBlamedOnBlackSquirrel-Choctaw.html
">Black Squirrel Story</A></B>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Choctaw legend about the origin of solar eclipses.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><B><A HREF="
http://temagami.nativeweb.org/tale-folklore-12.html
">Cooking Indian Squirrels</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Algonquin folklore about squirrels.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"  ALT="*"><B><A HREF="
http://www.ocbtracker.com/ladypixel/oldsqui.html
">Old Man and the Roasted Squirrels</a>:</b> <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Blackfoot legend about the culture hero tricking gullible squirrels into becoming his meal.
<BR>

<H2><U>
Recommended Books of Squirrel Stories from Native American Myth and Legend
</u><BR><font size=2>Our organization earns a commission from any book bought through these links</font>
</u></H2>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0826336914/natilangofthe-20
">Rabbit Plants the Forest</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Children's picture book illustrating a Cherokee legend about Rabbit helping Saloli the squirrel plant trees.
<BR>

<IMG SRC="dot5.gif"><b><A HREF="
http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1555911277/natilangofthe-20
">Native American Animal Stories</a>:</b><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Great collection of American Indian tales about animals, told by Abenaki storyteller Joseph Bruchac. 
